Diagram 3 (Capture and Take-Back)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In the previous diagram, white captures black's stone and black counter-captures.
\par
\par Now it is easy to see that white is dead.
\par
\par In response to your opponent's dansu, instead of connecting, it is a great move to hane. Please make yourself familiar with it and play in real games.
\par }
